1
00:00:11,833 --> 00:00:16,791
♪

2
00:01:35,166 --> 00:01:37,666
[NARRATOR] Four Saint Beasts
threaten to invade the Earth.

3
00:01:37,750 --> 00:01:39,166
The second's name is Byakko,

4
00:01:39,250 --> 00:01:41,000
a ferocious white
tiger who can destroy

5
00:01:41,083 --> 00:01:43,333
molecules with a
blast of his voice.

6
00:01:43,416 --> 00:01:45,333
Kuwabara stubbornly
took on this beast

7
00:01:45,416 --> 00:01:46,833
through a series of battles,

8
00:01:46,916 --> 00:01:49,958
the last of which took place
in Byakko's smoldering lair.

9
00:01:50,041 --> 00:01:52,250
In a daring move
Kuwabara knocked the beast

10
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:53,833
into a pool of molten lava,

11
00:01:53,916 --> 00:01:56,083
barely clinging
to his own life.

12
00:01:56,166 --> 00:01:57,958
The mission continues.

13
00:02:06,875 --> 00:02:08,958
Those boys are amazing sir!

14
00:02:09,041 --> 00:02:11,041
Ogre! That's enough
with the optimism!

15
00:02:11,125 --> 00:02:12,916
Go do something useful!

16
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:15,791
Do you suppose they'll make it
all the way through Maze Castle?

17
00:02:15,875 --> 00:02:17,041
Do you sir?

18
00:02:17,125 --> 00:02:19,208
Unfortunately I can't
suppose anything

19
00:02:19,291 --> 00:02:21,166
because we never
found any information

20
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:22,916
on the Four Saint Beasts.

21
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Now what do you suppose
is in your hand there?

22
00:02:25,083 --> 00:02:27,958
Oh yeah, uh sir I meant to
tell you about it earlier,

23
00:02:28,041 --> 00:02:30,500
yeah, turns out we do have
a little something written

24
00:02:30,583 --> 00:02:31,541
about the Four Saint Beasts!

25
00:02:31,625 --> 00:02:33,083
What?! Two whole battles

26
00:02:33,166 --> 00:02:35,791
and you're only now
telling me about this?!

27
00:02:35,875 --> 00:02:40,458
[KOENMA] No, Fig, Flour,
Four Saint, ah-page 42.

28
00:02:43,708 --> 00:02:46,916
Instructions, a very difficult
but rewarding challenge

29
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:50,041
with only one real
weakness. Hard to boil.

30
00:02:51,583 --> 00:02:53,916
[KOENMA] This says
Four Saint Beets.

31
00:02:55,583 --> 00:02:56,875
You've given me a cookbook!

32
00:02:56,958 --> 00:02:58,791
Oh sir!!

33
00:02:58,875 --> 00:03:00,500
One hundred spankings.

34
00:03:00,583 --> 00:03:04,583
Oh please sir, have mercy on
me! Anything but spankings!

35
00:03:04,666 --> 00:03:06,625
Maybe you misread it!

36
00:03:17,625 --> 00:03:19,666
What?! You're kidding me!

37
00:03:25,916 --> 00:03:28,875
It appears we have found
a maze in Maze Castle.

38
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:30,416
Well I guess that makes sense.

39
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:33,750
We must beware...
It's something of a legend.

40
00:03:34,833 --> 00:03:36,958
[KURAMA] In the beginning,
before the barrier wall

41
00:03:37,041 --> 00:03:39,208
was erected around
the city, hundreds of

42
00:03:39,291 --> 00:03:42,000
bounty hunters came
in search of the beasts.

43
00:03:42,083 --> 00:03:43,458
None succeeded...

44
00:03:43,541 --> 00:03:45,333
But the beasts never
left their tower,

45
00:03:45,416 --> 00:03:47,250
letting anyone who
made it into the castle

46
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:50,125
forfeit their lives
to this Maze.

47
00:03:55,958 --> 00:03:57,750
[KURAMA]
There are fifteen doors,

48
00:03:57,833 --> 00:03:59,958
all but one leads to a dead end.

49
00:04:00,041 --> 00:04:01,958
There are no second attempts.

50
00:04:02,041 --> 00:04:05,250
Unavoidable traps line
the incorrect passageways...

51
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:10,625
[bounty hunter
cries out in pain]

52
00:04:13,041 --> 00:04:17,083
[KURAMA] So you see, a poor
choice seals our fate.

53
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:22,125
Okay Mr. Sensitive,
this one's all yours.

54
00:04:35,916 --> 00:04:38,333
[KUWABARA THINKS] That door's
got a big feeling behind it.

55
00:04:38,416 --> 00:04:41,041
Kinda like the
first two monsters.

56
00:04:41,541 --> 00:04:43,291
The second door on the left.

57
00:04:43,375 --> 00:04:44,875
You heard the man! Let's go!

58
00:04:44,958 --> 00:04:47,041
[HIEI] How do we know he's
not making a mistake?

59
00:04:49,166 --> 00:04:51,083
I'm sorry shorty,
maybe it's not your thing

60
00:04:51,166 --> 00:04:53,541
but you're just gonna have
to trust me on this one.

61
00:04:53,625 --> 00:04:57,125
I know, there's somethin'
big behind that door.

62
00:04:57,208 --> 00:04:58,833
Somethin' scary.

63
00:05:01,166 --> 00:05:04,166
[mouse chirps]

64
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:05,541
I hate mice!!!

65
00:05:07,166 --> 00:05:10,875
Gee Kuwabara, and that speech of
yours was getting so dramatic!

66
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,791
[SUZAKU]
Very surprising.

67
00:05:15,875 --> 00:05:19,041
Somehow they have
chosen the correct door.

68
00:05:19,125 --> 00:05:22,083
We can hardly have it said
that the Four Saint Beasts

69
00:05:22,166 --> 00:05:25,416
welcome guests so
far into their home.

70
00:05:27,083 --> 00:05:30,791
I'm sorry, the Two Saint
Beasts is more accurate now.

71
00:05:31,583 --> 00:05:34,083
[SEIRYU]
I shall take them, master?

72
00:05:34,166 --> 00:05:36,666
You and I both know
that Genbu and Byakko

73
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:39,916
had become soft in these
years of containment.

74
00:05:44,583 --> 00:05:48,166
[SEIRYU] Their tenderfoot
mistakes shall not be repeated.

75
00:05:51,708 --> 00:05:54,250
[car horns honking]

76
00:06:22,125 --> 00:06:23,541
[BOTAN] I'm afraid
the news isn't good.

77
00:06:23,625 --> 00:06:25,458
The Makai Insects
are moving too fast

78
00:06:25,541 --> 00:06:28,875
for me to battle everyone
who's been taken over.

79
00:06:28,958 --> 00:06:31,625
All I can do now is contain
them into one part of the city.

80
00:06:31,708 --> 00:06:33,000
Very well...

81
00:06:33,083 --> 00:06:35,041
We'll just have to hope
Yusuke destroys the whistle

82
00:06:35,125 --> 00:06:37,083
before the city
bursts into flames.

83
00:06:37,166 --> 00:06:38,541
[KOENMA]
But that's no guarantee,

84
00:06:38,625 --> 00:06:41,000
so keep exterminating
what you can.

85
00:06:41,083 --> 00:06:43,333
I understand, over and out.

86
00:06:59,833 --> 00:07:01,750
Are we supposed to be scared?

87
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:04,500
Perhaps, that is the
mark of the Blue Dragon.

88
00:07:04,583 --> 00:07:08,041
And judging from the odor
I'd say the beast is inside.

89
00:07:08,125 --> 00:07:10,458
Yeah and he doesn't
feel very nice.

90
00:07:26,916 --> 00:07:28,625
This fog's alive.

91
00:07:28,708 --> 00:07:30,083
Must be a form
of Spirit Energy,

92
00:07:30,166 --> 00:07:32,541
coming from our beast's body.

93
00:07:32,625 --> 00:07:36,125
[SEIRYU] You have done very
well to come this far.

94
00:07:36,208 --> 00:07:40,000
But I shall no longer allow
you to disgrace my master.

95
00:07:40,083 --> 00:07:42,083
Where's that voice coming from?

96
00:07:42,166 --> 00:07:44,791
I don't know--
Come out now Dragon!

97
00:07:44,875 --> 00:07:47,500
This whole hide-and-seek
thing's getting pretty lame!

98
00:08:00,583 --> 00:08:01,958
As you request.

99
00:08:03,041 --> 00:08:04,875
A giant!!

100
00:08:04,958 --> 00:08:06,833
You may call me Seiryu.

101
00:08:06,916 --> 00:08:10,041
I am here now to end
your lives intruders.

102
00:08:11,666 --> 00:08:15,125
Well, he's no dragon.
But he is ugly.

103
00:08:15,208 --> 00:08:18,875
[SEIRYU] It is not wise to say
such things to your executioner.

104
00:08:21,291 --> 00:08:23,666
It appears we have
another guest.

105
00:08:25,583 --> 00:08:29,583
[panting]

106
00:08:32,166 --> 00:08:36,750
Guys I'm uh, not sure
how to tell you this, but...

107
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:38,333
[HIEI] It's coming
from behind us.

108
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:50,333
You must help me.

109
00:08:50,416 --> 00:08:52,333
You're joking.

110
00:08:52,416 --> 00:08:55,791
[BYAKKO] Please Seiryu,
these cowards,

111
00:08:55,875 --> 00:08:58,375
they tricked me in my own lair.

112
00:08:59,250 --> 00:09:02,208
They hid their true powers
from me until the end.

113
00:09:02,291 --> 00:09:04,041
You must help me recover.

114
00:09:04,125 --> 00:09:06,000
I knocked that guy into lava!!

115
00:09:06,083 --> 00:09:08,416
What does it take
to kill this guy?

116
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:12,000
Weakling! How dare you
dishonor us further!

117
00:09:12,083 --> 00:09:14,000
Please Seiryu!!

118
00:09:14,083 --> 00:09:17,833
You are no longer wanted here.
You are a disgrace!

119
00:09:18,666 --> 00:09:21,583
No Seiryu, I can help
you destroy them!

120
00:09:21,666 --> 00:09:23,125
It was a small mistake!

121
00:09:24,166 --> 00:09:26,625
Ice Dragon!!!

122
00:09:35,125 --> 00:09:36,208
What the...?

123
00:09:37,208 --> 00:09:40,958
[Byakko cries out in pain]

124
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,625
He's frozen!

125
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:03,291
You were right about
my fog of energy. 

126
00:10:03,375 --> 00:10:05,916
By lowering it
to subzero temperatures,

127
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,833
I can wrap my enemy in ice.

128
00:10:08,916 --> 00:10:10,041
You heartless bastard!

129
00:10:10,125 --> 00:10:12,416
How could you kill
off your own friend?

130
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:14,791
Seiryu.. why?

131
00:10:14,875 --> 00:10:16,750
[SEIRYU] He was a
weapon, not a friend.

132
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:19,666
And like a cheap sword,
he rusted.

133
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:28,708
This race of beasts
has no loyalty.

134
00:10:28,791 --> 00:10:32,166
Alliances are formed
strictly to gain power.

135
00:10:32,250 --> 00:10:34,000
I don't care what
kind of race they are.

136
00:10:34,083 --> 00:10:36,291
It's never right to
kill your own teammate,

137
00:10:36,375 --> 00:10:39,083
especially when they come
asking you for your help!

138
00:10:39,166 --> 00:10:42,458
This guy's pushed me too far!
He's dead!!

139
00:10:42,541 --> 00:10:44,750
[HIEI]
Save your anger.

140
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:48,333
You can take their leader.
I insist this fight be mine.

141
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:53,541
[SEIRYU] Ah.
Shall you be first, Hiei?

142
00:11:14,416 --> 00:11:15,750
What was that?

143
00:11:15,833 --> 00:11:19,291
Tell me you're not feeling
sympathy for this amateur.

144
00:11:19,375 --> 00:11:21,291
From your actions
at the Gate of Betrayal

145
00:11:21,375 --> 00:11:23,833
I was hoping you had more
of a warrior's spirit.

146
00:11:25,875 --> 00:11:27,583
He's a puzzle, isn't he?

147
00:11:28,916 --> 00:11:33,375
In times before I've seen
Hiei act with similar cruelty.

148
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:35,916
But something about
Byakko's execution

149
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,916
has caused great anger in him.

150
00:11:38,875 --> 00:11:42,125
Hiei seems to live by his own
code with very complex rules.

151
00:11:42,208 --> 00:11:43,791
But one thing is for certain.

152
00:11:43,875 --> 00:11:45,791
Never before have I
seen Hiei begin a fight

153
00:11:45,875 --> 00:11:49,625
using such an extraordinary
amount of his Spirit Energy.

154
00:11:49,708 --> 00:11:52,750
[YUSUKE] Good. As long
as he kicks some ass.

155
00:12:08,291 --> 00:12:11,916
I assure you, Hiei, it is not
too late to join our ranks.

156
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,708
Prostrate yourself
before my master

157
00:12:13,791 --> 00:12:15,416
and he shall you give
you power and fame

158
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:17,875
beyond what you
have ever tasted.

159
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:23,291
[HIEI] Is that all
you have to say?

160
00:12:24,625 --> 00:12:26,916
They're last words you know.

161
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,666
Fine! So that is your choice!

162
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:33,041
Then you shall meet your
death with the other weaklings.

163
00:12:45,458 --> 00:12:46,875
Hey! Be careful!

164
00:12:48,791 --> 00:12:50,458
Try blocking this!

165
00:12:53,541 --> 00:12:55,958
That freeze technique! Run!

166
00:12:56,041 --> 00:12:59,541
Ice Dragon!!!

167
00:13:04,166 --> 00:13:08,041
I'm sorry, I had forgotten
of your impressive speed.

168
00:13:08,125 --> 00:13:10,250
Now let's try again!

169
00:13:31,583 --> 00:13:34,083
He's gonna turn the whole
room into a hockey rink!

170
00:13:34,166 --> 00:13:35,916
Not just the room!

171
00:13:36,958 --> 00:13:39,083
Man I wish I had my jacket back!

172
00:13:39,708 --> 00:13:40,666
Hiei--

173
00:13:46,708 --> 00:13:47,583
Hey, he's okay!

174
00:13:47,666 --> 00:13:49,625
Yeah, don't scare
us like that!

175
00:13:49,708 --> 00:13:54,250
No, his leg. He won't be
able to run away anymore.

176
00:13:59,791 --> 00:14:05,416
You see, no one ever escapes.
Only beg for mercy.

177
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:08,916
With your leg frozen
you can't possibly move.

178
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:11,583
I suggest you start groveling.

179
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:16,958
What can he do?

180
00:14:17,041 --> 00:14:18,750
Ice Dragon!!

181
00:14:25,166 --> 00:14:26,583
Now you end!!

182
00:14:39,791 --> 00:14:41,000
Hiei!

183
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:45,458
You have escaped.
But you are wounded.

184
00:14:45,541 --> 00:14:46,375
[Hiei laughs]

185
00:14:46,458 --> 00:14:47,750
Why are you laughing?

186
00:14:49,666 --> 00:14:52,375
So what if your ice trick
can kill your wounded friend.

187
00:14:52,458 --> 00:14:54,250
It won't kill me.

188
00:14:57,083 --> 00:15:02,916
That's impossible!
I shall give one final blow!!

189
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:07,208
I don't think so.

190
00:15:20,916 --> 00:15:22,541
When did he attack?

191
00:15:23,291 --> 00:15:24,583
Don't feel bad Kuwabara,

192
00:15:24,666 --> 00:15:27,375
I couldn't see it either
after the initial hit.

193
00:15:29,166 --> 00:15:31,250
Shorty's a lot cooler
than I thought!!

194
00:15:44,791 --> 00:15:47,500
You made french
fries out of that guy!!

195
00:15:47,583 --> 00:15:50,083
Hiei how many times
did you cut him?

196
00:15:50,791 --> 00:15:52,791
Only sixteen.

197
00:16:03,208 --> 00:16:04,875
[YUSUKE]
Sixteen?

198
00:16:04,958 --> 00:16:09,041
Damn it, and here I could only
keep track of seven or eight.

199
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:10,375
That's nothing meager.

200
00:16:10,458 --> 00:16:13,375
After the first hit I
only saw flashes of light.

201
00:16:13,458 --> 00:16:15,458
I couldn't even see the flashes!

202
00:16:15,541 --> 00:16:17,291
Man, this isn't good.

203
00:16:17,375 --> 00:16:19,708
If you use those moves
the next time we fight

204
00:16:19,791 --> 00:16:21,583
I'm gonna be screwed!

205
00:16:21,916 --> 00:16:23,208
Maybe.

206
00:16:23,791 --> 00:16:24,833
Hiei.

207
00:16:24,916 --> 00:16:26,416
I thought for sure
he was going to say--

208
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:28,375
"Well of course you fool!"

209
00:16:28,458 --> 00:16:31,041
Hiei is going through
a tricky change.

210
00:16:32,125 --> 00:16:34,791
It appears he is
beginning to like you.

211
00:16:51,125 --> 00:16:53,708
[SUZAKU] This ceases
to be entertaining.

212
00:16:53,791 --> 00:16:56,458
These nothings
are ruining my plans!

213
00:17:00,625 --> 00:17:01,833
Suzaku! I'm back!

214
00:17:03,875 --> 00:17:05,083
What is it?

215
00:17:05,166 --> 00:17:06,583
You sound gloomy.

216
00:17:06,666 --> 00:17:09,458
Guess I don't need to ask
if the guests are still here.

217
00:17:10,791 --> 00:17:15,583
That's true Murugu. All my men
have been killed. Now go away.

218
00:17:15,666 --> 00:17:16,916
Not just yet!

219
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,291
I have gathered
the information you

220
00:17:18,375 --> 00:17:21,375
requested on Yusuke Urameshi.

221
00:17:26,625 --> 00:17:29,416
[MURUGU] It turns out our boy
wonder has few friends,

222
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:32,541
but one great weakness.

223
00:17:32,625 --> 00:17:34,041
Her name is Keiko Ukimura,

224
00:17:34,125 --> 00:17:37,750
and she's very close
to Yusuke's heart.

225
00:17:37,833 --> 00:17:40,500
She is pretty.

226
00:17:40,583 --> 00:17:41,875
I suppose so.

227
00:17:41,958 --> 00:17:44,916
The important part is he'll
do anything to save her.

228
00:17:46,458 --> 00:17:47,541
[SUZAKU]
Good.

229
00:17:47,625 --> 00:17:49,708
Then why don't we
test his concentration.

230
00:17:49,791 --> 00:17:53,000
How well will he fight
here inside Maze Castle.

231
00:17:53,083 --> 00:17:57,708
While back on the Earth.
His dear Keiko screams in agony.

232
00:17:57,791 --> 00:18:01,166
I know the perfect song to play,
on this Makai Whistle.

233
00:18:01,250 --> 00:18:06,791
It's titled Prelude to
Keiko's Suffering, in A Minor.

234
00:18:15,875 --> 00:18:18,833
Listen to me Koenma!
I have to abort this mission!

235
00:18:18,916 --> 00:18:20,708
The humans taken over
by the Makai Insects

236
00:18:20,791 --> 00:18:22,375
are starting to work together,

237
00:18:22,458 --> 00:18:24,625
and their numbers
continue to grow!

238
00:18:24,708 --> 00:18:27,416
Understood! Get yourself
to higher ground Botan!

239
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:29,375
I can't afford to lose you now!

240
00:18:29,458 --> 00:18:31,458
My thoughts exactly!

241
00:18:34,083 --> 00:18:36,250
Botan! I said run!!

242
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:39,041
I'm not sure how
feasible that is.

243
00:18:40,666 --> 00:18:42,125
[KOENMA]
Botan!

244
00:18:54,291 --> 00:18:56,375
And where do they
think they're going?

245
00:18:58,958 --> 00:19:01,000
Yusuke's middle school.

246
00:19:04,625 --> 00:19:07,333
[IWAMOTO] Miss Ukimura.
You're still at school?

247
00:19:07,416 --> 00:19:09,125
Yes, Mr. Iwamoto.

248
00:19:09,208 --> 00:19:13,250
Go on home and get some sleep.
Our big test is tomorrow.

249
00:19:13,333 --> 00:19:14,791
You want to score high

250
00:19:14,875 --> 00:19:17,125
and bolster our school's
ratings, don't you?

251
00:19:17,208 --> 00:19:20,791
Just as soon as I finish my
student council work, sir.

252
00:19:20,875 --> 00:19:25,791
Any news on Urameshi? I notice
he's skipped for several days.

253
00:19:25,875 --> 00:19:27,458
I don't know anything about him.

254
00:19:28,416 --> 00:19:29,916
Perfect.

255
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,958
He's a roach, Ukimura.

256
00:19:32,041 --> 00:19:34,958
I'd hate for you to be
infected with his disease.

257
00:19:35,041 --> 00:19:36,458
Yes sir.

258
00:19:45,541 --> 00:19:47,625
These flyers will be perfect.

259
00:19:48,291 --> 00:19:52,875
[door opens]

260
00:19:52,958 --> 00:19:56,916
Mr. Iwamoto... You...
look... pale.

261
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:03,083
I said... you need to...
get some sleep!

262
00:20:03,166 --> 00:20:04,833
O... kay...

263
00:20:24,166 --> 00:20:26,833
You've been spending too
much time with that cockroach.

264
00:20:26,916 --> 00:20:28,750
He's made you bad... Yes...

265
00:20:28,833 --> 00:20:31,250
You will need... correction.

266
00:20:34,041 --> 00:20:36,750
[KEIKO THINKS] Something is
very, very wrong here.

267
00:20:39,625 --> 00:20:41,291
Ukimura.

268
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:54,666
They must be those fanatics they
mentioned in the newspaper!

269
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:57,291
But, how do they know my name!

270
00:21:00,708 --> 00:21:04,166
Wait Ukimura. It's time
for your detention.

271
00:21:11,708 --> 00:21:13,625
What now? Got cramps?

272
00:21:13,708 --> 00:21:15,958
My whole brain just
felt like an ice cube.

273
00:21:16,041 --> 00:21:20,250
Something bad's happening,
I think back on Earth.

274
00:21:20,333 --> 00:21:22,250
No telling how
long we've been here.

275
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:24,208
The beasts have most
likely organized

276
00:21:24,291 --> 00:21:26,458
a counter assault
using the Makai.

277
00:21:26,541 --> 00:21:29,583
Only one more,
let's not waste time.

278
00:21:34,541 --> 00:21:36,958
[YUSUKE THINKS] I just hope
Keiko's all right.

279
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:39,000
[NARRATOR] Yusuke
is right to worry.

280
00:21:39,083 --> 00:21:40,750
With the power of
the Makai Whistle,

281
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:42,791
the last Saint Beast
has redirected

282
00:21:42,875 --> 00:21:44,250
the entire zombie army

283
00:21:44,333 --> 00:21:48,416
to one sinister goal:
the death of Keiko.

284
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:53,375
[BOTAN]
Things are getting nasty

285
00:21:53,458 --> 00:21:55,500
as the fight with the Saint
Beasts reaches it's peak!

286
00:21:55,583 --> 00:21:57,583
I'll do my best
to keep Keiko alive,

287
00:21:57,666 --> 00:22:00,625
while Yusuke confronts the
fiercest beast of them all!

288
00:22:00,708 --> 00:22:03,958
Suzaku! He's the mastermind
behind this entire invasion,

289
00:22:04,041 --> 00:22:05,958
and if Yusuke doesn't
do something quickly,

290
00:22:06,041 --> 00:22:09,458
his entire city could
go up in flames!

291
00:22:09,541 --> 00:22:11,041
But all isn't lost!

292
00:22:11,125 --> 00:22:14,166
It's Yusuke's first big fight
since his training with Genkai,

293
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:17,333
and our first chance to see the
new powers at his finger tips!

294
00:22:17,416 --> 00:22:20,333
That's next time,
on Yu Yu Hakusho!

295
00:22:22,583 --> 00:22:27,541
♪

